Sentencas: Cathode plays an important role in solid oxide fuel cell performance.
Titulo: (LaSr)xMnO3 cathode stoichiometry effects on electrochemical performance in contact with AISI 441 steel interconnect

Sentencas: This work studies the stoichiometry effect of (LaSr)(x)MnO3 (LSM) cathode on its electrochemical behaviors at 800 degrees C by investigating the interfacial reaction of an AISI 441 interconnect/LSM electrode/yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte half-cell structure.
Titulo: (LaSr)xMnO3 cathode stoichiometry effects on electrochemical performance in contact with AISI 441 steel interconnect

Sentencas: Ohmic resistance and polarization resistance of the cathodes are analyzed by deconvoluting the electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) data.
Titulo: (LaSr)xMnO3 cathode stoichiometry effects on electrochemical performance in contact with AISI 441 steel interconnect

Sentencas: The results show that the polarization resistance is dominant for decreasing the half-cell performance.
Titulo: (LaSr)xMnO3 cathode stoichiometry effects on electrochemical performance in contact with AISI 441 steel interconnect

Sentencas: Microstructure and phase analyses show that A-site excessive LSM sample experiences stronger bonding with the YSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: (LaSr)xMnO3 cathode stoichiometry effects on electrochemical performance in contact with AISI 441 steel interconnect

Sentencas: Energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy analyses reveal that Cr species first deposits and then is incorporated into the cathode perovskite structure by replacing Sr in the structure.
Titulo: (LaSr)xMnO3 cathode stoichiometry effects on electrochemical performance in contact with AISI 441 steel interconnect

Sentencas: Based on the above observations, the interaction mechanisms for the AISI 441 interconnect/LSM electrode/YSZ electrolyte tri-layer are proposed.
Titulo: (LaSr)xMnO3 cathode stoichiometry effects on electrochemical performance in contact with AISI 441 steel interconnect

Sentencas: Overall, the A-site deficient LSM stoichiometry is preferred for cell performance improvement.
